statement.p:
If n is a positive integer, define
\omega_k = \cos \dfrac{2\pi k}{n} + i\sin \dfrac{2\pi k}{n}
for k = 0,~1,~2,~ \cdots,~ n-1.  Show that (\omega_k)^n = 1. (We call \omega_k an n^{th}
 root of unity.)
